column5: Hello I'm new to the site and I was told by another member that I should introduce myself, so here it goes. My name is Ryan I'm 26 and love to fish. My dad got me into fishing at a really young age and I was hooked, just can't get enough. So this is my first question for the board. I'm planning on to nanicoke on Monday, I have been there once but can not remember the name of the launch that's right beside the power plant. Any help would be great and if anyone has fished it in the past couple days what's catching the fish and were would be great. Thanks!!   Ryan
Welcome to the board & good luck never been myself, but some day I'll make a drive SBK
Hoovers Marine Welcome to OFC August 6&7 is the Dofasco Bass Derby, Tickets are $10.00 this year. The weight scales are at Hoovers and Austin Park I have tickets
Thanks fish farmer that's it I knew it but I just couldn't remember it. Have u fished it lately???
